"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-prediction-another-medal-for-team-south-africa-tonight-mondy-5-august-prudence-sekgodiso-breaking-exclusive-betway-odds\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbPrediction: Another medal for Team South Africa TONIGHT?  South Africa could add to its medal tally at the Paris Olympics 2024 in the women's 800m final on Monday, 5 August.  South Africacould add to its medal tally at theParis Olympics 2024in the women's800mfinal onMonday, 5 August.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  Prudence Sekgodisowill attempt to emulate compatriotCaster Semenyain winning gold in the race which is scheduled for21:37(SA time).  Semenya won gold in the two-lap race in both 2012 in London and 2016 in Rio de Janeiro.  Sekgodiso, still only 22 years of age, is a rising middle distance star who has enjoyed a breakthrough season in 2024.  It came as no surprise to many to see her cruise through the heats and semi-finals and reach the final.  Leading South African bookmakersBetwayhave installed Sekgodiso as the fourth-favourite for the race.  Great Britain'sKeely Hodgkisonin the overwhelming favourite for gold at9/100, followed by Kenya'sMary Moraa (63/10)andTsige Duguma (12/1)of Ethiopia.  Sekgodiso can be backed at128/5.  Meanwhile, following a jam-packed weekend of action at the\\u00a0Paris Olympics 2024,\\u00a0Team South Africa\\u00a0finds itself in a tie for29thplace in the medal table alongsideKazakhstan.  South Africa have won a gold, a silver and two bronze medals to date.  The gold and silver medals were won byTatjana Smithin the women's 100m breaststroke and 200m breaststroke, respectively.  The men'srugby sevensteam as well asAlan Hatherlyin the men's mountain bike cross country won the bronze medals.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"